nt-size:11pt">       Building Stability</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">9</span><br /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">       Extradition</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">20</span><br /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Shared Prosperity</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">21</span><br /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">       Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">21</span><br /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">       Climate and Energy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">21</span><br /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Working Through Our Network to Achieve Our Objectives</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">23</span><br /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">       Staffing across the US Network</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">23</span><br /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">       Soft Power</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">24</span><br /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Conclusion</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">26</span><br /><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Introduction</span><br /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.47pt; padding-left:10.88pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Foreign and Commonwealth Office is grateful to the Foreign Affairs Committee for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the opportunity to contribute</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to its Inquiry into Government Foreign Policy Towards the United States. The US relationship is our single most important bilateral relationship. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It is a strong alliance built over generations and in many fields of activity.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It is a relationship that supports the achievement of our international objectives and the prosperity of our economy. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">At its heart, the US-UK special relationship is an alliance of value</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">: values of freedom, of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the importance of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">maintaining international peace and security, of maki</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ng sure that we live in a rules-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">based world. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> It is based upon</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> extensive historical, cultu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ral and people-to-people links.  The United Kingdom thus </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">work</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s very closely with the United States</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> across </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the full scope of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">our foreign and defence polic</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ies and on our shared objectives in the area of prosperity.</span><br /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.47pt; padding-left:10.88pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We have set out below information </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">addressing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e four strands of your Inquiry.  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 19pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he extent to which the UK’s foreign policy approach to the US has changed under the Coalition Government, and with what results for UK national interests, especially with respect to areas of unique UK-US cooperation;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he relationship between the UK Government’s policy towards the US and its increased focus on UK relationships outside the Transatlantic area;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">H</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ow the UK Government is responding, and should respond, to the US ‘pivot to Asia’; and</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">H</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ow, in its relations with the US, the UK Government can build on the lessons of post-2001 interventions involving both states in third countries.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 19pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:14.18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We would be happy to provide more detail on any point. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We look forward to the opportunity to supplement this evidence when the Committee holds oral hearings following its visit to the United States.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 1.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The Bilateral Relationship</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.21pt; padding-left:12.14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The United States remains the United Kingdom’s most important bilateral ally.  As the Prime Minister said on his visit to Washington in May 2013, it is a “</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">partnership without parallel</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">”.    </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.21pt; padding-left:12.14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Historically, the US and UK have worked together on some of the world’s greatest challenges.  We continue to do so.  O</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ur diplomats and intelligence agencies work together, our soldiers </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">serve</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> together, our scientists </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">collaborate</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, and our businesses trad</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e with each other</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The values of democracy,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> rule of law, and free markets have shaped our approach, and we continue to defend these values and advance our shared interests.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.21pt; padding-left:12.14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The relationship is strengthened through the personal links between our peoples.  Through our common language, our shared spirit of innovation and creativity, our popular culture and sport, our nations have always had a special affinity that continues </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to grow.  An estimated 829,000 British citizens live in the US, with around 180,000 US citizens living in the UK.  Over 3.7 million Britons visited the US in FY2012/13, and 2.8 million Americans visited the UK in 2012.  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.21pt; padding-left:12.14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Our economies are inexorably linked</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.  T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he US remains the largest investor in the UK, and the UK is the US’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> number one investment destination in Europe.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> We have almost one trillion dollars invested in each other’s economies, supporting over 1 million jobs in both the UK and US.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> The US is the UK’s top export destination for both goods and services.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.21pt; padding-left:12.14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he UK’s ability to achieve its international objectives </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is significantly improved</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> if we share </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">those objectives with the US.  For</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">se reasons,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> maint</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">aining a strong T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ransatlantic relationship has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">long been a cornerstone</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> of British foreign policy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Cooperation between the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">British and US governments</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">remains</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> second to none.  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.21pt; padding-left:12.14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The 2012 Presidential elections saw President Obama re-elected</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to serve a second term.  The President has set out priorities for his </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">second term </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">focusing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> on continuing economic recovery with a programme of balanced fiscal consolidation and targeted public investment.  Jobs and growth remain his top priorities, in a clear parallel with UK objectives.  Immigration reform and an ambitious approach to international trade policy are also priorities for the President’s second term.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Foreign Secretary has already built a strong relationship with the new Secretary of State and former Chair of the Senate Foreign Relations Committee, John Kerry.  They have met many times since Secretary Kerry’s appointment in February, and speak regularly on the top foreign issues.  2013 will have seen t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he P</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rime Minister</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Deputy Prime Minister, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Foreign Secretary, Chancellor, Defence Secretary and Home Secretary </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">all </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">me</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">t their </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">opposite numbers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in Washington</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> during the course of the year.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Many other </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Ministers from across Whitehall </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">have established early contact with</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> their</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">new </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">counterparts.  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">President Obama has set out his foreign policy priorities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> for his second term</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> In speeches in 2013 the President has highlighted</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">defeating Al Qaeda and its allies; stopping Iran from obtaining nuclear weapons; drawin</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">g down US troops in Afghanistan,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> reviving the Middle East Pea</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ce Process,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and promoting democratic transitions across the Arab world.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> These are goals shared by the UK and we welcome the significant effort the US Administration has put into trying to achieve them. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Both President Obama and Secretary Kerry have also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">devoted much time to the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> ongoing crises in Syria and Egypt.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Further afield</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, the Administration has continued its policy of ‘Rebalance’ to Asia, including through </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">working towards </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e early conclusion of the Trans-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Pacific Partnership trade deal. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">As an extension of this, the Administration is looking to reinforce its efforts in Latin America, as set out in a speech by Vice President Biden in May.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In May, President Obama said </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the US continues to value “</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">a strong UK in a strong European Union</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">” and agree</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">d</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> with the Prime Minister’s goal of a reformed, outward-looking EU.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  D</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">uring President</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Obama</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">’s visit to Africa in July he stressed his desire to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">help increase </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">investment in the continent, including via the Trade Africa initiative. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The UK-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">US economic and financial relationship remains extremely strong. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Our close collaboration in the wake of the financial crisis has been important in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">supporting the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">progress</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> we have made since 2010</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to tackle deficit and debt, and to support economic recovery, jobs and growth</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In other areas too, the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">factors underpinning UK-US co</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">operation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">remain</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> strong. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> On energy, we both want secure, sustainable sources of energy to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ensure </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">national security and economic prosperity</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">B</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">oth the US and UK </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">are working to achieve</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> a global agreement on the post 2020 Climate Framework in 2015 and we work closely together in support of this challenging objective</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> while recognising the differences in our national positions and the UK’s position within the wider EU. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Looking to the future, the relationship will be further strengthened as the EU and US embark on the largest and most significant </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">free </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">trade deal in history, the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.  T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he UK </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">demonstrat</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> a clear leadership role in this undertaking</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, and o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ur guidance and coordination led to the successful launch of negotiations at the June G8 summit at Lough Erne. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">A comprehensive deal could be worth up t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">o £10 billion to the UK economy.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The strategic foreign policy objectives of HM Government and the Obama Administration are closely aligned. But there will inevitably be occasions when foreign policy priorities and the political context in the US and UK differ, and when we therefore choose to pursue different courses of action.  But the foundations that bind us so closely together – our deep trade and investment linkages, our shared values, our linguistic and cultural histories – remain.  Indeed, these factors all underpin our ability to maintain an honest and open dialogue, even when we disagree.  This is rare among international partners and is valued by both sides.  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 1.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 1.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 1.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Our Objectives</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Government’s overriding objective in its relations with the United States is to continue a strong, close, and frank relationship that brings concrete benefits for the UK and advances our shared objectives.  To achieve this we will continue to:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 19.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Work with the US to safeguard Britain’s national security and support UK objectives worldwide;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Help build Britain’s prosperity;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Provide modern and efficient services to British citizens in the US;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Facilitate</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> understanding and communication between the UK and the US; and</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Promote</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Britain’s standing and reputation in the US to build our influence across the country.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Among our specific </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">foreign and security policy objectives</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> we aim to:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Strengthen the bilateral defence relationship;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Maintain close collaboration with US security authorities to reduce the threat to the UK from terrorism, organised crime, and cyber attacks;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Coordinate closely on the top foreign policy issues, including the Middle East Peace Process, Syria, Iran, Afghanistan, and Iran;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Increase cooperative engagement with the US in Asia, and support our broader objectives with the emerging powers; and</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Leverage</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> US influence in support of the UK’s objectives in international institutions, including through our Presidency of the G8 and the Foreign Secretary’s Preventing Sexual Violence in Conflict Initiative.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="18" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Our </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">prosperity objectives</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> include a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">commitment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Increase UK exports to the US, and inward US investment into the UK;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Make significant </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">progress</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> on negotiations towards an ambitious EU/US Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Maintain the UK’s position as the US’s scientific, cultural, and education partner of choice;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Encourage the US to play a leadership role in international climate negotiations;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Increase collaboration on energy governance, security, and research; and</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Promote</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> UK academic institutions in the US, including through the Marshall Scholarship programme.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">To provide modern and efficient </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">services to UK nationals</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in the US we will:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Provide a high quality consular service;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Ensure the US network is ready to respond effectively to natural disasters or other types of crisis such as terrorist attacks;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 37.2pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Campaign against use of the death penalty, with particular focus on cases involving British Nationals.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Working Together o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">n Foreign Policy Priorities</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 1.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="20" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Foreign Secretary set out his vision for an enduring UK-US relationship in the context of a changing world in June 2013 at the Reagan Presidential Library. The speech reaffirmed the UK position that foreig</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">n policy is not a zero-sum game.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> B</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">oth the UK</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">’s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and US’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> increasing focus on </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">strengthening</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> relationships</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">around the globe will not be at the expense of our deep</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> bilateral</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> relationship. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Rather, the stronger our relationships are elsewhere in the world, the more we can do to support each other as allies across the full range of shared interests. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Furthermore, the strength of the UK-US relationship means that the leaders of our countries can</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, as the Foreign Secretary said in his speech,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> ‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">share thinking about how to maintain clear leadership, bold thinking and decisive foreign policy in a shifting world’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Clearly the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Middle East and North Africa region </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">represents a significant focus for our cooperation.  The region </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">has witnessed major change since the Arab Spring began in 2011, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">driven</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> by citizens demanding their political and economic rights. From the outset of the Arab Spring, the UK and US have shared a common goal in working to support more democratic, accountable societies in the region, as a route to long-term stability and prosperity. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Our</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">approaches</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">towards</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> countries that have experienced revolutions ha</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ve</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> been </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">closely</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> aligned, and we have worked together both bilaterally, and in multilateral </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">fora</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, notably the G8 Deauville Partnership to provide practical support for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the region. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Under the UK lead on the Deauville Partnership in 2013, we have built on the US’s Presidency last year, including </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">making progress</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> on </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Broader Middle East and North Africa</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">BMENA</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> civil society-government initiative.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="22" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The foreign policy issues discussed below represent only a selection of our joint work with the US, not the entirety of our cooperation.  Cooperation on Latin America, Sub-Saharan Africa, and many other parts of the world that are not covered below continues to be strong.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">MEPP</span></p><ol start="23" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Achieving a negotiated two-state solution to the Israeli-Palestinian conflict is an urgent foreign policy priority for both Britain and the US.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Over the past year, the Foreign Secretary has spoken repeatedly of the need for the international community to revive the peace process in efforts led by the United States and supported by European, Arab and other nations.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Secretary Kerry has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">now </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">led successful efforts to resume formal negotiations, with a view to resolving all final status issues. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="24" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Foreign Secretary has welcomed the focus Secretary Kerry</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> with the support of President Obama</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> has brought to bear on the MEPP</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Foreign Secretary and Secretary Ker</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ry discuss the issue regularly.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Secretary Kerry also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">updated</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> EU Foreign Ministers </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">at the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Gymnich</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in Vilnius on</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">7 September 2013</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Officials in London, Washington and the region </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in close contact </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">with their counterparts across the US government to share information, ideas and expertise on the MEPP.   </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Syria</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span></p><ol start="25" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Since the conflict in Syria began over two and a half years ago, the US and the UK have been at the forefront of international efforts to tackle the crisis, including close co-ordination on the use of chemical weapons by the Assad regime. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> We</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">have shared </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">objectives </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> are focussed on getting the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">international community </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to unite to bring all sides together to achieve </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> political solution that is needed to end the conflict</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.  We strongly support</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> US efforts to organise a second Geneva conference.  Although </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the British Government’s position on involvement in military action in response to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the use of chemical weapons</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> is clear</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, the UK will </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">continue to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">be highly active in addressing the Syria crisis, making the case internationally for a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">robust</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> response.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="26" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The UK and the US </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">are two of the largest providers of humanitarian assistance </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to those affected by the conflict in Syria </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">we</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> will work intensively with the US</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> including at the UN, to secure aid access and address the shortfalls in funding.  We continue to lead the core group of eleven countries most actively supporting the Syrian National Coalition opposition gro</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">up and will also continue to co</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">operate to counter the threat of extremism from Syria.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 19.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Iran</span></p><ol start="27" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Iran – in particular its nuclear programme </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">an important area of foreign policy co-operation between the UK and the US.  We consult closely on the E3+3’s approach to the nuclear negotiations, but also on how the international community can address the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">military threat from the Iranian nuclear programme through the effective implementation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of sanctions.  Without strong UK-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">US cooperation, we and our partners would have been less effective on Iran policy.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="28" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Our cooperation on Iran also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">includes exchanges on political and economic developments (including President </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Rouhani’s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">recent </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">election), </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the human rights situation in the country</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, and Iran’s foreign policy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> - in particular in relation to current instability in Syria, Lebanon and the wider Middle East</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Libya</span></p><ol start="29" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In Libya itself, through our Embassies in Washington and London, and through direct contact at Ministerial and official levels, the UK and US governments work closely together to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> support the Libyan people and g</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">overnment at this critical stage in the country’s transition to a stable, democratic and prosperous state.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Our Embassies in Tripoli have an exceptionally good working relationship – the political and military teams work particularly closely together and the Ambassadors make joint calls on the Prime Minister and other </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">government</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> figures to emphasise </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">our</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> common objectives.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="30" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Following up the agreement at the G8 meeting at Lough Erne, when the Prime Minister and President Obama met Libyan Prime Minister Ali </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Zeidan</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, we have developed our training proposals for the Libyan army together and presented our ideas and concerns to the Libyans jointly. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This has helped </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">mobilise</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the Libyan system so that we can get the training programme started as quickly as possible. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="31" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This close working relationship also extends to dealing with </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">at times very dangerous security situation on the ground in Libya.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Our Embassies in Libya work very closely together in assessing the security situation in Libya and alter their security pos</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ture accordingly, as well as co</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ordinating public and political activity.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Egypt</span></p><ol start="32" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The UK and US share an interest in a stable, prosperous, secure and democratic Egypt that plays a positive role in the wider region.  We have had close and long-standing cooperation with the US on Egypt, including regular and broad-ranging discussions at official and Ministerial level as part of our wider foreign policy </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">dialogue</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.  We have worked together closely in response to the events in Egypt on 3 July.  Like us, the US is deeply concerned about the situation in Egypt.  The UK supported recent EU and US-led efforts to reach a peaceful resolution in Egypt.  We continue to work together with Egyptian interlocutors and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">our partners, including the US G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">overnment, to support the swift return of a democratically-elected civilian government.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Iraq</span></p><ol start="33" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The US and UK have common aims in Iraq: to enhance its stability and develop its democratic institutions, to enable it to realise its economic potential, and to encourage it to play a positive and constructive role in the region.  We have both pressed the Government of Iraq to exercise restraint in dealing with the ongoing Sunni protests, and establish a political process for addressing the protestors’ legitimate demands.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Likewise, we have worked together to encourage </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the Iraqis </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to do everything possible to prevent Iranian support reaching the Assad regime via Iraq.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="34" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The US and the UK share concerns over the difficulties in the relationship between the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Government of Iraq </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and the Kurdistan Regional Government, and we have a joint interest in resolving ongoing disputes.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The UK has also worked with the US to assist Iraq’s efforts to normalise its relations with countries in the region and the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">United Nations Security Council</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Afghanistan</span></p><ol start="35" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> The UK supported the US intervention in Afghanistan </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in 2001 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and provided a significant number of troops to the initial phases of Operation Enduring Freedom and throughout the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">period of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">International Security Assistance Force combat missio</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">n in Afghanistan. This close cooperation and co</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ordination is continuing through the transition to Afghan security lead and the drawdown of all international combat forces by the end of 2014. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="36" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Throughout the last 12 years, the UK and US have worked to shared o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">bjectives in Afghanistan and co</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">operated on all aspects of our work, including support to the Afghan National Security Forces, counter-terrorism, counter-narcotics</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> rule of law, development assistance and support to Afghanistan’s political system.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span styl