#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:96.4pt"><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">469</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:175.15pt"><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">171</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:58.75pt"><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">640</span></p></td></tr><!--[if !supportMisalignedColumns]><tr style="height:0pt"><td style="width:95.35pt; border:none"></td><td style="width:96.4pt; border:none"></td><td style="width:175.15pt; border:none"></td><td style="width:58.75pt; border:none"></td></tr><![endif]--></table><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 19.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Notes:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">i)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">FCO US Network figures include 60 UK-based FCO staff in Washington and 18 in the Network.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ii)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The M</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">O</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">D</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> has 130 personnel based in the Washington Embassy (included above).  There are a further 573 MOD personnel working in the United States not supported by the FCO Network of posts.  These range from military personnel in operational units or headquarters and exchange officers in each of the Service to technical experts working on joint acquisition projects.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">iii)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The figures provided are a snapshot of the named posts data as recorded on 31 July 2013.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">There may be some discrepancies with current figures, in particular between numbers of FCO and other government department locally-engaged staff.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="90" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The FCO regularly reviews the size and make up of our footprint in the US to ensure we are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">achieving</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> our objectives in the most efficient and cost effective way possible. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Recent shifts in the network include the opening of the Seattle office and increased resources in Washington to engage with the US’s activity in Asia.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 19.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 1.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Soft Power</span></p><ol start="91" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">To achieve our policy objectives in the US, the FCO seeks to influence not just those who make the decisions, but also those who shape the environment in which those decisions are made, and those who will shape it in the future.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">A </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">key</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> part of this work is the Marshall Scholarship programme that seeks to build networks of long term influence for the UK in the US.  The programme has run since 1953 and enables talented postgraduate students from the US to study in the UK.  There are Marshall scholar alumni in each branch of the US federal system, including Deputy Secretary of State Bill Burns and Associate Justice of the Supreme Court Stephen </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Breyer</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.  LinkedIn founder Reid Hoffman </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a Marshall scholar.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="92" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The make-up of the US population is changing, becoming even more diverse</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, and will make the US a minority-majority nation by 2050.  The Hispanic community is predicted to grow the fastest, tripling from 42 million in 2005 (16% of the population) to 128 million in 2050 (30%).  The Asian population will also nearly triple to around 40 million 2050 (9% of total population). It </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">has been argued that this shift </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">could</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> lead to a decline in the UK’s influence with the US, as elites from this group look more naturally to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">South America and Asia</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> rather than across the Atlantic.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Our US Network play an important role in ensuring that we continue to understand</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">se</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> changing demographics, and retain our ability to influence.  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="93" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">I</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">n Texas</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> for example,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Hispanics are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">currently </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the largest minority group (38%) and growing fast.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Their influence in politics and business is already strong. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The British Consulate General</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in Houston </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ha</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> worked hard to engage with leaders and influencers in this demographic and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">we </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">were delighted to host San Antonio Mayor and Democratic Party </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">member</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, Julian Castro, in London last year.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Their </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">outreach work into Hispanic media and business groups is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">also</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> paying dividends.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> The UK has a great reputation and standing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> – </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the challenge is to ensure that the emerging political and business classes from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">acros</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s the demographic spectrum see us as a partner of choice in the future.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 19.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 19.2pt"><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="579" height="266" alt="" /></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 19.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 19.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 19.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="94" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Traditional diplomatic tools are not the only or most effective means of reaching the widest audience.  The US Network is a leader in digital diplomacy, using modern and innovative forms of communication to forward and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">promote</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> our objectives.  The visit of HRH Prince Harry was an example where social media was used to achieve maximum </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">impact</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and reach.  Using the full array of its digital platform – including Twitter, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Facebook</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Flickr</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Storify</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> – the Embassy was able to bring the visit to many more people than conventional forms of communication would have reached alone.</span><br /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:center"><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="579" height="423" alt="" /></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="95" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Our Network also works closely with the British Council throughout the United States, with the aim of continuing to build engagement and trust in the UK.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> UK-US cultural relations have always been important and are now even more so with the changing US demographics.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> The relationship needs to be refreshed to ensure the UK is relevant to the growing Hispanic population in years to com</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> The British Council plays an important </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">role in helping UK partners and stakeholders in the fields of culture, arts and education gain access to the US.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Council also supports the work of the GREAT campaign in the US.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-transform:uppercase">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Conclusion</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="96" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The UK-US bilateral relationship is in good health.  As this document has sought to illustrate, we remain essential and valued partners in taking forward our objectives across a vast range of issues and regions of the world.  It is also critical to our national security, our prosperity and our defence capability.  In short, it is a relationship from which we benefit.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="97" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Our ability to work together with the US is based upon our shared values, our shared history and our shared objectives. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">As set out above, t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he UK’s ability to achieve its international objectives </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is significantly improved</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> if we share </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">those objectives with the US.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Addressing MPs and Lords in Westminster Hall during his state visit to London in May 2011, President Obama described </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the US-UK relationship </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> as “</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">one of the oldest, one of the strongest alliances the world has ever known</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">”.  We continue to work to ensure that the relationship remains strong, close, and frank, in order that both </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">our </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">countries continue to benefit from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> partnership.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-27.15pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="98" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.88pt; padding-left:5.47pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The FCO welcomes the Committee's continuing interest in the UK-US bilateral relationship and looks forward to its report.  We stand ready to provide supplementary material as required at any s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tage during the Inquiry.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">3 October 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>